summary:
Fixed the deadlock.

Cause: TransferService locked the two accounts in the order (from → to).  
Two simultaneous opposite-direction transfers (A→B and B→A) could therefore lock A then wait for B, while the other locked B then waited for A ⇒ circular wait → deadlock.

Fix: Impose a global lock order. Always acquire the lock of the account whose id is lexicographically smaller first, independent of transfer direction.

Key change in app/TransferService.java:

```
Account first, second;
if (from.getId().compareTo(to.getId()) < 0) {
    first = from; second = to;
} else {
    first = to; second = from;
}

synchronized (first.getLock()) {
    ...
    synchronized (second.getLock()) {
        ...
```

Re-ran test.sh: both passes succeed, no deadlock, balances conserved.

All good.
